            <thetext>To reproduce:
1. Save and open file given in URL in Opera 11
2. Click on element labeled &quot;focus on mousedown&quot;
3. Click on element labeled &quot;focus on click&quot;

Expected:
The elements should be focused, but no automatic scrolling should happen.

Actual:
The element labeled &quot;focus on mousedown&quot; is scrolled to the top edge of the 
containing div when clicked. Curiously, this does not apply to the element 
labeled &quot;focus on click&quot;.

Tested on Mac, confirmed on Windows and Linux.

This issue is related to bug 4518.</thetext>
